summary:
Inktober day 8 Star/Third eye
Today's prompt was a little special. Because all I could think about was jirachi and how it was...
body:
Inktober day 8 Star/Third eye

Today’s prompt was a little special. Because all I could think about was jirachi and how it was the first pokemon movie my grandmother got for me. My mom had bought the first movie for me almost immediately but after that it wasnt till wishmaker that I was able to get another pokemon movie. So I dedicated this to my grandma who I miss dearly…

summary: From 10/08/18 - 10/11/18, the TwitchPresents marathon is LIVE this week with Pokémon Advanced Chellenge! Episodes from season 7...
body:
From 10/08/18 - 10/11/18, the TwitchPresents marathon is LIVE this week with Pokémon Advanced Chellenge!

Episodes from season 7 include more Pokémon contests, Misty & Togepi visiting Hoenn, a Skitty catch, Flannery’s first gym leader battle, a crying Torkoal, the gang going back to Petalberg City, a cute Bulbasaur for May, Tailow’s evolution, Winona’s battle in the skies, and much much more!

13 episodes per day (from Monday-Thursday) will rerun in multiple times just so you won’t miss the stream depending on your schedule.

Watching with Twitch chat could be the best (or worst) experience you’ll ever have! But if you want a more comfy chat experience, feel free to talk/chat about the marathon in my Pokémon Discord server PokéTōku —> Invite link here :)

summary: Lotamen Lotad and Ramen fusion Nutritional information: Type: Pasta/Meat Type Ability: Noodle Constriction -  Noodle...
caption:
Lotamen

Lotad and Ramen fusion

Nutritional information:

Type: Pasta/Meat Type

Ability: Noodle Constriction -  Noodle Constriction prevents all foes from fleeing (including Teleport) or Switching Out while the Pokefood with this Ability is on the field.

Signature Move - Ramen Rave - it shoot its foodie contents at the opponent, lowering the opponent’s speed and accuracy. Pasta Type.

The Ramen Carrier Pokefood

Lotamen loves to share the contents in its bowl with others.  It usually stays within reach of a restaurant so then it can replenish the contents in is bowl, however it will travel to other places if it feels that the ramen is not good enough for it.

So, day one of the Halloween event and we have Lotad and ramen suggested by @offshore4am. This one was a lot of fun to make.

blog.name: inikavulpixelreviews
blog.title: Let's Talk About Pokemon!
blog.description:
Reviewing my personal opinion on every single Pokemon! Yes, all 809 of them!
(Mostly) Daily Uploads, 3 PM EST.

summary: Let’s Talk About Pokemon - Skiddo and Gogoat
title: Let’s Talk About Pokemon - Skiddo and Gogoat
body:
672: Skiddo

Here’s another line that doesn’t really surprise much. Goat kid? Sure, goat kid. A cute goat kid. The handlebar horns are kinda funny, considering this Pokemon evolves into one known for being ridden. It’s just an animal plus element that’s pretty standard fare by now.

Personal Score: 6.5/10

Sure.

673: Gogoat

Which is about the best name in the entire Pokemon franchise if you ask me. But the rest of it doesn’t live up to said name, sadly. It’s still got the handlebar horns, but it’s otherwise just a goat that happens to be grass type. Could’ve been goofier given it was a goat but ehh. While the beard is fun, it’s got painfully normal eyes compared to actual goats. It’s not a huge deal but a bit more goat-face would’ve given this thing a bit more personality.

Personal Score: 6.5/10

Go, goat.

Overall:

Not a pair that was that big a deal. Though now I realized something. It’s one of THESE TWO that should’ve been Pokemon #666!!! That would’ve been HILARIOUS. Just Gogoat, an otherwise normal goat Pokemon that just happens to be number 666 and JUST SO HAPPENS to be the symbol of Satan. I might’ve liked Gogoat better had that been the case alone, haha. That is asking for a ridiculous amount of bravery from Gamefreak but god. Can you imagine?

[Archive]
